verbose_text: No statistically significant difference in haemoglobin level : P = 0.225, mean corpuscular volume : P = 0.266, haematocrit : P = 0.090, total erythrocyte count : P = 0.219, serum iron : P = 0.212 and binding capacity of iron : P = 0.212 between patients with enteropathy and normal small bowel findings was observed.
